title: The Grateful Dead Live at Fillmore East on 1971-04-27
description:
Set 1

Truckin', Mama Tried, Bertha, Next Time You See Me, Cumberland Blues, Me And Bobby McGee, Loser, Hard To Handle, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Casey Jones

Set 2

Sugar Magnolia, Deal, Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Playing In The Band, Dire Wolf, Searchin'*, Riot In Cell Block #9*, Good Vibrations**, I Get Around**, Help Me Rhonda*, Okie From Muskogee*, Johnny B. Goode*, Sing Me Back Home, Uncle Johns Band > Turn On Your Love Light

*with the Beach Boys
**Just the Beach Boys: Good Vibrations, I Get Around.

reviews.review_text: Nobody has reviewed thus yet? This is freakin' awesome! The Dead and the Beach Boys? I wish my Dad was still around to hear this! Great recording.
A great concert What a show!  This would've been so much fun to go to.  And the Okie tune...what an F-U to the conservative population to have the hippiest of all bands performing it.

3rd night of five "Ladies" shows. It's the end of the week that things got hot and this is the first indication of that. Two songs from this one were used for the Skull Fuck album and three for Ladies & Gentlemen. 1st set. Truckin' is a surprisingly jazzy version, considering American Beauty hadn't been out long. A tease into Cryptical becomes a straight-faced rendering of Mama Tried. Bertha is the version on Skull Fuck but this is the undubbed original. Same for Bobby McGee, here with the original guitar. China Cat tries to start for nearly a minute but it's the peak of the set (hard to believe it wasn't plucked for Skull Fuck). The 1st Set then has its own Casey Jones encore while the second set has none! (Ladies Disc#4 puts the Bill Graham rap from the 29th here). 2nd Set. The continual breaks and fuckin' around from the first set lay over into the second, mainly from the arrival of Beach Boys, whose middle-of-the-set songs are a disaster and excised for this purpose (nobody is playing OR singing the same verse on Johnny B Goode). After a mediocre show, in typical Dead fashion they come back after the Beach Boys leave and end with one of the best Lovelights ever (in my Top 5, fwiw)! It has a major Pig rap but is also weirdly tightened up. 1st Set:  B- 2nd Set: B (not counting seven Beach Boys songs, else D-) Overall = 3 1/2 Stars Highlights: Me & Bobby McGee (undubbed version of Skull Fuck track) China>Rider (25th is better but this is still A-) Me & My Uncle (the one from 29th is on Skull Fuck but this one's better) Dire Wolf (tight, albeit straight) Uncle John's>Lovelight (incredible; on Ladies Disc#2) Sources: the Boswell-Smith sounds clearer than the Miller to me, if not a touch too EQ'd.

Tape Reels This is my first time on this site in my search for info..  I'm a fan of all things reel to reel especally when it comes to the Dead.  I recently acquired a box of tapes from these shows, all on Scotch tape with printed artwork and set list on the inside recorded at 71/2ips. They sound amazing!  Considering the amount of recording that went on I realize locating the source is a long shot.  
Just wondering if anyone has any idea on other places for information to track down who may have done this??
